    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <head>No. 24.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hubbard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tolcio</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-09-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 29, 1887</date>. (Received September
                                    29.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Hubbard acknowledges the receipt of Mr. Bayard’s instruction No.
                                153, of August 19, 1887, and requests, at the instance of the
                                Japanese Government, copies of the Treasury regulations and
                                contracts concerning the seal fisheries, and also a more definite
                                statement as to the nature of the protection which it is desired to
                                extend to those fisheries.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
